<h2>About GCAVC</h2>                    
<p>Gujarat Chess Association for Visually Challenged (GCAVC) was founded in 2013 by visually impaired chess players of Gujarat. It has been working for the upliftment of blind chess and chess players in the state. When it was established, Gujarat had only 4 internationally rated visually impaired chess players. However, in the last 10 years, this number has grown to over 50 and continues to increase.</p>                
